ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Details of the nature of this woman's potential exposure to
BSE-contaminated meat are awaited.

As of February 2009 in addition to the 5 deaths in Spain, there have
been 165 vCJD deaths in the UK, 23 in France, 4 in the Republic of
Ireland, 3 in The Netherlands, 2 in Portugal, and single deaths in
Italy, Canada, Saudi Arabia and Japan
(<http://www.cjd.ed.ac.uk/vcjdworld.htm>. In addition, 2 cases in the
USA are thought to have been contracted elsewhere.

An interactive map of the provinces of Spain showing Cantabria (S on
the map) and Leon (LE on the map) in the north of the country can be
viewed at:
<http://flagspot.net/flags/es(prov.html>. - Mod.CP]
